VPC Peering
=============
1.Requester of VPC peering connection
2.Acceptor of VPC peering connection.

>The owner of the acceptor VPC peering connection must accept the request for the peering connection to be active.
>There should be no CIDR overlap between acceptor and requestor VPC
>The security group of both the VPC should allow to flow to/from acceptor/requestor VPC
>A vpc cannot be used as a transit point.

VPC Peering lifecycle
======================

init---->Pending--->provisioning------>active
  |        |           |                  |
  Failed   Expired     rejected           |
                                      deleteting
                                          |
                                        deleted
                                           |
                                       no longer available

Limitations of vpc peering
============================
1.There is a vpc peering connection quota.
2.Between 2 vpc we cannot have more than one VPC connection.

VPC Peering Combinations
1.Same account and same region
2.Same account different region
3.Different account and same region
4.Different account and different region

VPC peering connection status goes to failed state if there is a overlapping CIDR.
VPC peering request expire after 7 days.





